Careers













 NYSE:  OLN
        
          
        
          
        









Menu















Olin offers a variety of jobs and career paths that will appeal to those who are drawn to a creative, energetic and open workplace environment. Olin is always interested in hiring the best and most enthusiastic talent available, offering prospective employees exciting opportunities to grow and prosper within a dynamic company. Learn about available career opportunities in our career opportunities section. 

Olin is absolutely committed to diversity within its work force and to providing equal employment opportunities to all employees and job applicants. This applies to every phase of the employment process - from hiring and training to compensation, promotion and disciplinary action. 

Olin Corporation's Chlor Alkali and Winchester Divisions offer job opportunities for all qualified applicants, including college students participating in co-op plans, INROADS participants, and skilled craftsmen.

 
Search Job Listings  

Recruiting Scam Advisory
Please be advised that unauthorized individuals may attempt to use the Olin Corporation (“Olin”) name or brand, as well as the name of Olin directors and
employees, in an attempt to secure personal or financial information, or money,
from job seekers.   These scammers use a variety of tactics,
including posting false job postings on job boards and other locations, and
sending unsolicited emails, text messages or other communications to job
seekers, falsely representing themselves to be affiliated with Olin.  
The following are some important signs to look for in
determining whether you may be the target of a scam:

Check the email address origin. Olin
     employees should have an email address ending in @olin.com or @olinbc.com.
      Scammers will try to make very similar email address domains, so
     make sure to check that it is from a @olin.com or @olinbc.com address.
A communication requests money for placement fees,
     recruiting, or in exchange for guaranteed employment.  Any communication
     requesting any amount of money in exchange for employment with Olin
     is fraudulent.  Olin never charges candidates fees, or
     requires payments of any kind in order to secure employment.
A communication requests payment as a fee for
     certification, training materials or other work-related expenses. Olin
     does not require payment for any materials as part of its recruiting
     process.
Requests for tax, bank account or credit card
     information. Olin recruiters do not require
     the completion of tax forms, or request bank account or credit card
     information as part of the recruiting process.  As a precaution, we
     recommend you do not disclose personal or financial details to anyone in
     response to an unsolicited email request.
Offers work from home opportunities. Olin
     does not currently offer any work from home opportunities.

You may also have been contacted
directly by a scammer who may have obtained your resume through a resume
database. As a federal contractor, Olin is committed to equal opportunity
employment and all valid, open positions will be posted on our website (www.olin.com) and all interested applicants must
apply on-line.  We do not accept paper applications except in limited
circumstances and we do not directly solicit individuals for any role that is
not posted on our website. We do not conduct interviews via text or an instant
messaging application (like Google Hangout). 
If you are contacted regarding a fraudulent employment proposal
or have been the victim of a recruiting scam, you are encouraged to alert your
local law enforcement agency.
The Federal
Trade Commission also has a reporting service on their website for those
who have been targeted by a recruiting scam. 
 
Benefits

Olin salaried employees enjoy competitive salaries and generous benefits, in a challenging and positive work atmosphere. Headquartered in Clayton, MO, Olin has major facilities in Alabama, California, Canada, Georgia, Illinois, Louisiana, Mississippi, Nevada, New York, and Tennessee.


         

College Recruiting 
Olin Corporation is always looking for talented individuals to join our team. We regularly recruit at certain college campuses throughout the U.S., seeking individuals with the background, energy and creativity that will carry our company forward. 

If you're a college student nearing graduation and are interested in learning if your talents might fit with Olin, please visit our job listing section and apply on-line. 


“Olin is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.”














 
